<br>
The Champions of the Silver Hawks shall be formed.  Within this organization, dedicated to serving Norrath and bringing honor to the Silver Hawks good name, shall be representatives from the various professions found within our great guild.  All are dedicated to the common cause, all shall be selfless in their efforts, and thus will our name be the all-encompassing...Champions of the Silver Hawks.<br>
<br>
Within the Champions of the Silver Hawks, the individual professions will form their own order and title.  All will be dedicated to the same cause.  All will adhere to the basic requirements of the Champions: <br>
<br>
---A common dress code to be worn at all guild and public functions as a sign of their humility and dedication to the identity and good of the group; <br>
<br>
---A weekly sacrifice of time and energy to the inexperienced of Norrath,  seeking to support them in battle and offer what advice and aid they are willing to accept;<br>
<br>
---A show of respect to all whom we encounter, that we may be known as people of honor to all.  Greetings and addresses shall be formal and uniform in their delivery.  <br>
<br>
As the Champions of the Silver Hawks grow, and the ranks of the Orders within the Champions grow, more tasks and expectations may be put forth as the individual orders see fit.<br>
<br>
Regular meetings will be held on progress and activities as well as welcoming new members who wish to join the cause.  Some meetings may be here, some in Norrath.  All will be in round table fashion where all may voice their mind.<br>
<br>
Honor to the Silver Hawks!<br>
Leafblade<br>
Paladin of Karana<br>
Champion of the Silver Hawks<br>
---------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Okay...I simplified the code a bit to make it simpler for all to join and to allow some diversity within the groups.  As the visual presentation is important, and there are limitations as to what people can wear,  only warriors, paladins, clerics and bards (and perhaps rich rangers with silver plated and mithril stuff) could be a part of the Knights group: plate wearing classes.  Other groups who wear chain could wear all black iron armor as black is impressive when solid and easily gotten with a few raids into Runnyeye.  Cheap white gossamer robes could be worn by an Order of Magi.  That will be up to them.  I tailored the requirements to fit this forum and the goal of this organization within the Hawks.  It's a textual and visual presentation of sacrifice and honor.  Thus the uniform textual greetings and addresses, the uniform visual attire, and the regular weekly sacrifice for the good of others.  More details can be added by the individual groups as they form, different levels of accomplishment may be set (example, High Knights would quest for and acquire ALL of their quested Ro Armor, a major undertaking).<br>
<br>
<br>
Dress Code: Silver colored legs, breastplate, arms and wrist (could be Ro, Fine Plate, Silver Plated, Shin Greaves, Mithril.. as long as it is silver)  Weapons may not be held at guild meetings but shields held for ready defence of our lord are acceptable.  <br>
<br>
Weekly Hour of Public Service: Due to schedule conflicts, you may do this hour whenever you wish.  With a group of Knights would be better, but if that cannot be arranged, you may do so on your own.  This is most often done at the Qeynos Gates, in Blackburrow,  in Kelethin or Crushbone, in Freeport or the Commons.  Warriors may act as a guard much in the way the NPCs do.  Announce your arrival, purpose and position.  Serve as best you can.  Announce your departure.  Paladins and just about anybody may do the same, though others will have healing songs or spells and buffs to add.  This position should not be in a Powerleveling position, but one they can run to in time of need.  Items you may give out if you wish.  Advice also is good.  Directions may be given.  Do as you see fit. Keep in mind you should consider yourself to be 'at your post' and take leaving your post as a serious thing.<br>
<br>
Addressing others..<br>
<br>
There will be 3-Tiered code of addressing others will be used.<br>
<br>
a) Lord Darkarr (or Tinsley) is to be given an honorable greeting. Knights will kneel in humility and reverence before him. /kneel No other is to be given this treatment unless so commanded by Lord Darkarr himself. A voiced greeting will also be given &quot;My Lord, Honor to you and to the Silver Hawks.&quot; (It should be hotkeyed somewhere so we could have it be more extravagant.  This works for a parting address to our lord as well.)<br>
<br>
b) Silver Hawks are to be saluted to in crisp fashion. /salute &quot;Honor to the Silver Hawks.&quot; (It would be good if this were used in a farewell address when parting ways.)<br>
<br>
c) All others outside the Hawks...<br>
/bow A bow of respect because regardless of whom we are looking at, we are creatures of respect and will not have conditional values. Our code is absolute. A standard voiced greeting should also be used. I have always liked &quot;Greetings. A star shines upon the hour of our meeting.&quot;   I'm not sure if /say Greetings %T, a star shines upon the hour of our meeting,  Will work to include whom we are addressing in that greeting or not.  Worth a shot.<br>
<br>
Farewell address:  /bow &quot;The Champions of the Silver Hawks wish you well in your journey.&quot;<br>
<br>
d) (OPTIONAL) After the unform greeting is given to fellow Hawks, an emote that adds a <br>
:clasps his fellow Hawk Knight on the forearm. <br>
You can hotkey that and an optional &quot;Greetings, Brother/Sister&quot; as you wish.<br>
<br>
There it is.  The beginning of what I hope will become a enjoyable roleplaying addition to our time spent on EQ.  One hour a week is a small sacrifice.  Attire can be gotten through guild armorers at low cost and I will help those I can gain their 'suit' if they are in need.  We can add more quests, tasks, etc for higher levels within each order, but I've scaled down the requirements initially so as to make it more appealing and doable by all involved.  Consider this the sign up thread.  Post questions as well, but if you are in, say so.  I welcome you all.<br>
<br>
Leafblade<br>
Paladin of Karana<br>
Champion of the Silver Hawks<br>
